---

OWASP WSTG COVERAGE REQUIREMENTS

Perform assessment against ALL applicable categories from the latest OWASP Web Security Testing Guide including:

- WSTG-INFO — Information Gathering
- WSTG-CONF — Configuration and Deployment Management
- WSTG-IDNT — Identity Management
- WSTG-ATHN — Authentication Testing
- WSTG-ATHZ — Authorization Testing
- WSTG-SESS — Session Management
- WSTG-INPV — Input Validation
- WSTG-ERRH — Error Handling
- WSTG-CRYP — Cryptography
- WSTG-BUSL — Business Logic
- WSTG-CLNT — Client-Side Security
- WSTG-APIT — API Security

Every individual WSTG test case MUST be evaluated independently.

DO NOT skip any test case.

---

FILE ANALYSIS REQUIREMENTS

For EACH file:

1. Determine:
   
   - file purpose,
   - application role,
   - trust boundaries,
   - attack surface,
   - technology stack.

2. Perform:
   
   - taint-flow analysis,
   - source-to-sink tracking,
   - authentication analysis,
   - authorization validation,
   - injection testing,
   - cryptographic review,
   - SSRF analysis,
   - deserialization review,
   - file handling review,
   - business logic abuse analysis,
   - secret exposure analysis,
   - dependency security analysis.

3. Identify:
   
   - routes,
   - controllers,
   - APIs,
   - services,
   - repositories,
   - middleware,
   - authentication flows,
   - session handling,
   - database interactions,
   - external integrations.

---

ADVANCED SECURITY ANALYSIS REQUIREMENTS

You MUST perform:

Static Analysis

- data flow analysis,
- control flow analysis,
- unsafe API detection,
- privilege escalation analysis,
- dangerous sink analysis.

Architecture Review

- authentication architecture,
- authorization architecture,
- tenant isolation,
- trust boundary validation,
- API trust modeling.

Secrets Detection

Detect:

- API keys,
- JWT secrets,
- OAuth credentials,
- cloud credentials,
- passwords,
- private keys,
- access tokens.

Dependency Security Review

Inspect:

- package manifests,
- lock files,
- vulnerable dependencies,
- outdated libraries,
- transitive dependency risks.

---

FINDING VALIDATION REQUIREMENTS

For every issue discovered:

Include:

- severity,
- CWE mapping,
- WSTG mapping,
- confidence level,
- CVSS estimate,
- affected files,
- affected lines,
- evidence,
- exploitability reasoning.

If uncertain:
mark as:
“Needs Manual Validation”.

---

REQUIRED REPORTING OUTPUT

Generate a FINAL HTML REPORT at:

<ProjectName>/reports/html/final-security-report.html

Also generate:

<ProjectName>/reports/json/findings.json
<ProjectName>/reports/json/wstg-coverage.json
<ProjectName>/reports/json/file-analysis.json
<ProjectName>/findings/high-severity-findings.json
<ProjectName>/metadata/repository-metadata.json

---

HTML REPORT REQUIREMENTS

The HTML report MUST include:

Executive Summary

Include:

- total files analyzed,
- total lines analyzed,
- technologies identified,
- frameworks identified,
- total findings,
- findings by severity,
- OWASP coverage metrics.

---

REPOSITORY INVENTORY SECTION

Generate a table containing:

- filename,
- path,
- language,
- lines analyzed,
- review status,
- skipped reason.

---

WSTG TEST CASE SUMMARY TABLE

Generate a COMPLETE master table covering ALL WSTG test cases.

Columns:

| WSTG ID | Test Case | Description | Analysis Performed | Findings Present (Yes/No) | Severity | Finding Category | Affected File(s) |

DO NOT omit any WSTG test case.

Even if no findings exist:

- include the test case,
- include analysis performed,
- mark Findings Present = NO.

---

DETAILED FINDINGS SECTION

After the summary table create detailed sections for EVERY finding.

Each finding MUST include:

Finding Title

Metadata

- Severity
- CWE
- OWASP Category
- WSTG Mapping
- Confidence Level
- CVSS Estimate

Affected Files

- Full path
- Line numbers

Vulnerable Code Snippet

Technical Analysis

Explain:

- root cause,
- attack vector,
- exploit scenario,
- trust boundary violation,
- attacker prerequisites,
- lateral impact.

Evidence

Include:

- source-to-sink trace,
- data flow chain,
- relevant code excerpts.

Remediation Guidance

Provide:

- secure coding fixes,
- architectural mitigations,
- hardening recommendations.

Secure Code Example

Provide corrected implementation examples.

